## 26. Video Player Strategy

The biggest technical risk is video memory management.

The app should not create a video player for every item.

Recommended active window:

```txt
1. Previous video
2. Current video
3. Next video
```

Maximum active players for MVP:

```txt
3
```

When current index is `i`, keep:

```txt
i - 1
i
i + 1
```

Dispose everything else.

---

## 27. Video Player Manager

```dart
class VideoPlayerManager {
  final Map<int, Player> _players = {};
  final Map<int, VideoController> _controllers = {};

  Player? getPlayer(int videoId) => _players[videoId];

  VideoController? getController(int videoId) => _controllers[videoId];

  Future<void> prepare(VideoEntity video) async {
    if (_players.containsKey(video.id)) return;

    final player = Player();
    final controller = VideoController(player);

    _players[video.id] = player;
    _controllers[video.id] = controller;

    await player.open(
      Media(video.videoUrl),
      play: false,
    );
  }

  Future<void> play(int videoId) async {
    final player = _players[videoId];
    if (player == null) return;

    await player.play();
  }

  Future<void> pause(int videoId) async {
    final player = _players[videoId];
    if (player == null) return;

    await player.pause();
  }

  Future<void> disposeVideo(int videoId) async {
    final player = _players.remove(videoId);
    _controllers.remove(videoId);

    await player?.dispose();
  }

  Future<void> disposeExcept(Set<int> keepIds) async {
    final idsToDispose = _players.keys
        .where((id) => !keepIds.contains(id))
        .toList();

    for (final id in idsToDispose) {
      await disposeVideo(id);
    }
  }

  Future<void> disposeAll() async {
    for (final player in _players.values) {
      await player.dispose();
    }

    _players.clear();
    _controllers.clear();
  }
}
```

---

## 28. Recommended Manager Lifecycle

For MVP, `VideoFeedPage` should own `VideoPlayerManager`.

```txt
VideoFeedPage
  └── VideoPlayerManager
```

Reason:

```txt
1. Easier lifecycle control
2. Dispose all players when feed page closes
3. Avoid global player memory leaks
4. Safer than singleton manager for MVP
```

Later, this can become a scoped service if needed.

---

## 29. Preloading Logic

When the current page changes:

```txt
1. Prepare current video
2. Prepare previous video
3. Prepare next video
4. Play current video
5. Pause previous and next videos
6. Dispose videos outside the active window
```

Pseudo logic:

```dart
Future<void> handlePageChanged({
  required int index,
  required List<VideoEntity> videos,
}) async {
  final current = videos[index];

  final previous = index > 0 ? videos[index - 1] : null;
  final next = index < videos.length - 1 ? videos[index + 1] : null;

  await manager.prepare(current);

  if (previous != null) {
    await manager.prepare(previous);
    await manager.pause(previous.id);
  }

  if (next != null) {
    await manager.prepare(next);
    await manager.pause(next.id);
  }

  await manager.play(current.id);

  final keepIds = {
    current.id,
    if (previous != null) previous.id,
    if (next != null) next.id,
  };

  await manager.disposeExcept(keepIds);
}
```

---

## 30. Video Quality Selection

Do not always choose the highest-quality Pexels video.

For mobile feed playback, choose a balanced source.

Recommended target:

```txt
720p or medium quality MP4
```

Avoid:

```txt
1. 4K videos
2. Very large files
3. Extremely low-quality files
```

Selection example:

```dart
VideoFileModel selectBestVideoFile(List<VideoFileModel> files) {
  final mp4Files = files.where((f) => f.fileType == 'video/mp4').toList();

  mp4Files.sort((a, b) {
    final aScore = (a.height - 720).abs();
    final bScore = (b.height - 720).abs();

    return aScore.compareTo(bScore);
  });

  return mp4Files.first;
}
```

---

## 31. Pagination Strategy

Recommended MVP pagination:

```txt
per_page = 8 to 10
```

Load more when:

```txt
currentIndex >= videos.length - 3
```

Reason:

```txt
1. Prevent loading too many large videos
2. Reduce memory pressure
3. Keep first API response fast
4. Give enough buffer for smooth scrolling
```

